(3,'Fret','fret','Musical Trio','<h2>Fret is an instrumental trio from Nepal, creating new forms of music, furnishing fusion grooves in an evolved manner.</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"img-fluid\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../../uploads/d2dcc0c1d0ac4d7aa15344ccbd5d3ce6.jpg\" alt=\"fret trio\" width=\"512px\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Fret Trio</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Fret is an instrumental trio from Nepal, creating new forms of music, furnishing fusion grooves in an evolved manner blending traditional and ethnic music with an influence of eastern classical, western music and world music through Sarangi, Flute and Newari drums. The trio&rsquo;s vision is to explore their instruments in an innovative way and exhibit it in their style. The trio constitutes three individual artists from diverse musical backgrounds combined together to form a distinct world music genre.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Nowadays, we can see our young Generations are getting detached from their own origin, of which music is a dominant aspect. To keep the ambience of Bhaktapur alive, music should be understood and learned. So,in order to understand anything, we have to spread knowledge about it. So the most effective way of doing so is to give it an academic direction. &lsquo;Ambience of Bhaktapur&rsquo; is an initiation designed by Fret with a motive to make the music and musical instrument known among students from their school level. We believe in giving musical knowledge about music from school level will develop an interest to learn music and even encourage them to pursue music as a profession too. Through this initiative we firmly believe in promoting our music and musical instruments into the world music scenario.That is why we are taking initiatives through schools of Bhaktapur.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>So,in order to understand anything, we have to spread knowledge about it. So the most effective The way of doing so is to give it an academicdirection. &lsquo;Ambience of Bhaktapur&rsquo; is an initiation designed by Fret with a motive to make the music and musical instrument known among students from their school level.We believe in giving musical knowledge about music from school level will develop an interest to learn music and even encourage them to pursue music as a profession too. Through this initiative we firmly believe in promoting our music and musical instruments into the world music scenario.That is why we are taking initiatives through schools of Bhaktapur.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>They have recently released their first debut album \'MOKSHYA\' literally translates as liberation which has eight songs. Fret has been performing their music in different local events, concerts, charity event and international collaboration. Young Generations of musicians having audacity to re - organise melody from traditional to new age. Fret as played their music at echoes in the valley, Dewar\'s, project NAADHE , radio photo patrika sathi etc. Fret has evolved themselves with open willingness to collaborate with artists of all forms and diverse art mediums as performance art, painting, installation etc</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"img-fluid\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../../uploads/752f1460800f46d889eb9e601a2a2c5b.jpg\" alt=\"Ambience of Bhaktapur\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Ambience of Bhaktapur</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/740be0d90aee4c1c94770a9357846e59.jpg\" alt=\"Ambience of Bhaktapur\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Ambience of Bhaktapur</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/a30ddcb468de4eedac8e6c2a09b738cd.jpg\" alt=\"Ambience of Bhaktapur\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Ambience of Bhaktapur</span></p>','Fret is an instrumental trio from Nepal, creating new forms of music, furnishing fusion grooves in an evolved manner blending traditional and ethnic music with an influence of eastern classical, western music and world music through Sarangi, Flute and Newari drums.',1,'fret33.jpg','2023-09-30 20:28:31','2023-10-03 09:59:15'),
(4,'Sushant Shree Rajbhandari (Ryan)','sushant-shree-rajbhandari-ryan','Multidisciplinary artist','<h2><span style=\"font-size: 24pt;\">His subconsciousness and spirituality are depicted in his pen and ink drawings, which are inspired by automatism and distortion techniques.</span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"img-fluid\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../../uploads/ryanwork2.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"512\" height=\"514\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"ql-align-center\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"ql-size-small\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 10pt;\">Ryan Rajbhandari</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"ql-align-center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sushant Shree Rajbhandari (Ryan) is a Multidisciplinary artist based out of Kathmandu with a BFA from Sirjana College of Fine Arts. He has worked on murals, experiential and interactive installation. He performs throat singing, plays the spoon, and other percussive instruments and is the Art Director of the experimental ethno-instrumental band called \'Stotram\'. Throughout his college years, he volunteered in a variety of art projects. In 2018, he participated in a cross-disciplinary international art residency called \'Expression Expedition,\' which was organized by the interdisciplinary art group \'Luna Poets.\' This experience exposed him to other forms of art in his practice, such as performance art, sound art, and installation art. He participated in a group exhibition at Roots Bar in 2019. He also traveled to Hong Kong to meet with an artist friend, and his interactions with the artists there shaped his worldview even more. In 2021, he participated in a young artist residency at the \'Bikalpa Art Center,\' which resulted in a duo exhibition titled \"Solace of Mind: Fractal Utopia.\" In 2022, he participated in Danfe Art&rsquo;s peer learning exchange program, which resulted in a public event called &ldquo;On Taking Flight.&rdquo; In 2022, he participated in a 6 month long mentorship program organized by Bikalpa Art Center called &lsquo;Trans Culture Camp&rsquo;, which resulted in a group exhibition in April, 2023. He participated in an International Art Camp organized by Crack International, Bangladesh in 2022. In 2023, he participated in a group exhibition and live painting session organized by Windhorse gallery, called &lsquo;Contemporary Creators.&rsquo; He was the recipient of the Special Award in Performance Arts awarded by National Academy of Fine Arts in 2023.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Rajbhandari\'s method incorporates REM sleep visualization experiments. His subconsciousness and spirituality are depicted in his pen and ink drawings, which are inspired by automatism and distortion techniques. His work contains recurring themes of masculine and feminine energies, mindfulness, neo-shamanism, neo-tribalism, animism, oneness, and fractals. His older works, on the other hand, portrayed darker aspects of his personality, such as melancholy, fear, grief, discomfort, anger, lust, and doom, as a result of anxiety, inferiority complex, and depression. For him, pursuing art has been a healing and expressive journey. Currently, he is fascinated in working and experimenting with installations and art performance.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"img-fluid\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../../uploads/ed8132aea58348fdbef86fd314537db1.jpg\" alt=\"The House Recognized Me\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Title: The House Recognized Me</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Medium: Arcylic</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Size: 11.5 x 16.5</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"img-fluid\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../../uploads/80b7a6ce8c2c4374a5e80311ac3b7ae4.jpeg\" alt=\"The Emotional Bodies\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Title: The Emotional Bodies</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Medium : Mixed Media</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Size: Variable&nbsp;Installation</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/7d8f488a22024b2cba10fa279a447d34.jpeg\" alt=\"Black Orb and the spirit\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Title: Black Orb and the spirit<br>Medium : Water Color and ink<br>Size: 8.3 x 11.7 inches<br></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/d7d4f4273b7d4668a702ffab81d1d1bc.jpg\" alt=\"A Classroom\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Title: A Classroom<br>Medium: Mixed (Interactive Installation)<br>Size: Variable</span></p>','Sushant Shree Rajbhandari (Ryan) is a Multidisciplinary artist based out of Kathmandu with a BFA from Sirjana College of Fine Arts. He has worked on murals, experiential and interactive installation. He performs throat singing, plays the spoon, and other percussive instruments and is the Art Director of the experimental ethno-instrumental band called \'Stotram\'. Throughout his college years, he volunteered in a variety of art projects.',2,'ryanwork2.jpeg','2023-09-30 20:39:40','2023-10-03 09:13:50'),
(5,'Mommin Pradhan','mommin-pradhan','Visual artist','<h2>But what is lost, can be found. I invite you to find connections with me, yourselves and with those around us; sharing and taking this experience with you, and embracing new ones. IN(within).<br>- MOMIN Pradhan</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"img-fluid\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../../uploads/9f65abad04544677a5e5b2b36a5358f8.png\" alt=\"Momin Pradhan\" width=\"512px\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Momin Pradhan</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To connect is not just a fundamental part of our life, but the very essence of it. In a way, our entire existence is a search for connections, a sense of belonging. We search for it in the relationships we make, in nature, and even within ourselves. This journey and its findings make up our human experience. However, at certain moments and phases in our life, for some reason or no reason at all, it feels like we have lost all our connections to life. This isolation and sense of dissonance amplifies one&rsquo;s solitude, the monotony of days, it warps our perception of time and space within our own loneliness. But what is lost, can be found. I invite you to find connections with me, yourselves and with those around us; sharing and taking this experience with you, and embracing new ones. IN(within) - MOMIN Pradhan</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Momin Pradhan is a visual artist currently pursuing his dreams in fine art. He explores, paints, designs, and experiments with various mediums. Many of his artworks are related to human emotion, experience, and exploration, sensory and perception - which invites you to be an observer of the self. Interested in experiments, exploring possibilities through paint and installations. Momin usually plays with the use of shades, space, and sounds. He is interested in persistent, complex, and uncomfortable human emotions such as longing, helplessness and vulnerability. His artworks explore how such emotions colour the way we perceive and respond to the world around us. He believes that exploration and understanding of such emotions help us to grow more confident and able as humans.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Pradhan has exhibited his works in numerous group shows, including &lsquo;Traces and &lsquo;Sang Sangai.&rsquo; He also collaborated with The Tehra family to execute and exhibit the &lsquo;Blessed Wonders I and II&rsquo; online exhibition. Most recently, he partnered with Project Naadhe to showcase his work in the &lsquo;White Noise&rsquo; exhibition, and he was featured in the group exhibition &lsquo;Impressions.&rsquo;&rdquo; and in the 2023 &ldquo;Young Artist Show&rdquo;. Within the depths of the human spirit lies a profound complexity of emotions and thoughts. Some of these emotions are too intricate, too overwhelming to put it out in the world, and thus we find ourselves retreating, concealing them from the world. We shrink within, isolating ourselves in a realm where our innermost thoughts echo, where the weight of our feelings engulfs us. In that solitude, a palpable silence that speaks volumes, in that there is peace, though heavy. In this, there are feelings hidden within, in pieces and in fragments. Small fragments stowed away amidst others. A story never to be seen again, a poem never to be read.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"img-fluid\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../../uploads/f21aeb4c7b7d41f38657056db1e82b07.jpg\" alt=\"From : NFA Young Exhibition\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">From : NFA Young Exhibition</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/d12cd955c24041c1a79333077da0d8d0.jpg\" alt=\"From : the young artist exhibition\" width=\"896px\" height=\"auto\"></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">From : the young artist exhibition</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>','Momin Pradhan is a visual artist currently pursuing his dreams in fine art. He explores, paints, designs, and experiments with various mediums. Many of his artworks are related to human emotion, experience, and exploration, sensory and perception - which invites you to be an observer of the self. Interested in experiments, exploring possibilities through paint and installations.',3,'momin.png','2023-10-03 10:16:07','2023-10-06 10:15:43'),
(6,'Sundar Lama','sundar-lama','Performance artist','<h2>Art created a profound impact on me immediately I enrolled into fine art college, where I got equipped with the skills and academic aspect of fine arts.</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/6898f2d9195c4cb2afd646b0a1977e3d.jpg\" alt=\"Sundar Lama\" width=\"768px\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Sundar Lama</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Before fine art I was very fascinated by tattoo art and I was a student of management back then. Once I met a friend who was practicing tattoo art. In order to learn more on art I started visiting art galleries. Later I searched for an institution which provided art education. That\'s s how I got into Nepal Fine Art College. I am very excited and concerned by the impact art can create to an individual. Art created a profound impact on me immediately I enrolled into fine art college, where I got equipped with the skills and academic aspect of fine arts. Today , I realise to know that merely learning skill is not enough to express oneself and creative experiences and imagination.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sundar lama was awarded Performance art &ldquo;Bronze&rdquo; in \"Without Borders\" International Art Competition Organized by School of Visual arts, World University of Design, Delhi NCR, India in 2020 and : A man with whistling tune , is his first Book as poet and also solo art exhibition exhibited at The taragaon museum,hyatt regence, Boudha, Nepal In 2019. Lama also received Arniko Youth Art Award(Gold medal)\" 2075 organized by the National Youth Service Trust. He is also an art teacher at school - I love interacting with children to give them new perspectives on life and colour thrills me.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I mostly observe and research on human behavior and their surroundings. Here at Nardevi the surroundings that I am in very much have a root in the ancient cultural continuation, the situation of contemporary Nepal. I use this observation and research as my methodology and incorporate carious cultural motifs, introducing the philosophical aspect in my art works. This is how I metaphysically explore the creative dimension. This exploration expanded even more in my master level art education. Today I trust my works stands on its own as an individual identity from other fellow artists. However, I use various significant elements which manifest the &ldquo;Nepaliness&rdquo; in my work. Exploring his creative identity through installation and performance art.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>He says : I am always happy to be around theatres, it adds colours to my life. I have collaborated with many artists but Collaborating with foreign artists from Bangladesh and japan was an eye opener to me. Those experiences on creating has changed me and I prefer to call myself a pluralist : who believes in initiating conscious experimentation by merging various genres of art such as performance, installation, video art and ofcourse painting as well.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/1323018394c042fb8baea8086f9ee9a6.jpg\" alt=\"Performance art of Sundar Lama\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Performance art of Sundar Lama</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/4ecc960609864b2ea6e3aa5bad9ac998.jpg\" alt=\"Performance art of Sundar Lama\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Performance art of Sundar Lama</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/f450c6d42a5b4003bacdca7e458d8dd8.jpg\" alt=\"Performance art of Sundar Lama\" width=\"768px\" height=\"auto\"></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Performance art of Sundar Lama</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>','\"My art works attempt to understand such invisible yet clear and delicate existential phenomena. In other words my art work is an interaction between space and consciousness. I am guided by my instinct, however I have a liberty to choose. From here begins the journey of the mind to the heartâ€¦..\"',4,'sundarlama1.jpg','2023-10-03 10:23:33','2023-10-06 10:38:48'),
(7,'Nirvita Shakya','nirvita-shakya','Visual artist','<h2>Nirvita Shakya is a Visual artist based in Kathmandu. While she is widely known for Performance art and Fabric art, she is equally proficient in Oil painting, Mixed media painting, Ceramic art, Sculpting, Installation art.</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/nirvitadp.jpg\" alt=\"Nirvita Shakya\" width=\"768\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Nirvita Shakya</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Nirvita Shakya is a Visual artist based in Kathmandu. While she is widely known for Performance art and Fabric art, she is equally proficient in Oil painting, Mixed media painting, Ceramic art, Sculpting, Installation art. She takes courage to explore her expression in mediums or forms, where she does not limit her concept to only one medium or materials. She creates subdued experience from surroundings and layered with poetic meaning, inviting interpretation and questions. She paid attention to the inner voice of humans and their dialogues and has carefully brought it into artform.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>She graduated in Fine Arts from Kathmandu University School of Arts and Design. She has also worked with Junk, collaborating with Association of Mechanical Engineering students for junk Art Projects, Samayojan-18. She also taught creative activities held in Srijana College of Fine Arts and participated in Performance art program based on New Media Arts with Artist from Taiwan. She has also done collaborative project with Project Nadhe &lsquo;White Noise&rsquo; through where she developed her performance art practices and vision evenly. She was featured artist in exhibition &lsquo;Impression&rsquo; held by KU, where she did five days long Performance Art in 2022. She has done a Print making exhibition in 2019, &lsquo;Traces&rsquo; in Park Gallery, Pulchowk. And Online group exhibition 2020 &lsquo;Blessed Wonders&rsquo; with Tehra Organization.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>She visited Artist residency in Bangladesh and has done Group exhibition on Kushtia Village of Bangladesh, &lsquo;Crack Internation Art camp&rsquo; in 2022 and her Solo exhibition in Khulna Arshinagar in 2023. Recently she has done fabric installation for the set of Massacre Macbeth in Mandala Theater with Wataru Ram Shrestha led by Greg Mitchell.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>She was approached for her performance art in Kalasha and has done Performance art &lsquo;Jatra&rsquo; in 2023. She is one of the exhibiting artists in the Young Artist show held by Mcube gallery in 2023. She believes that art helps to articulate thoughts and imagination.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/90f0c00aba6d44bd9368101db6347024.jpg\" alt=\"Bhumari Ma Rang A performance Art Purano Ghar Theater\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Bhumari Ma Rang</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">A performance Art</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Purano Ghar Theater</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/027c1ed502ad44ca9104c90434d1bf7b.jpg\" alt=\"Bhumari Ma Rang A performance Art Purano Ghar Theater\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Bhumari Ma Rang<br>A performance Art<br>Purano Ghar Theater</span></p>','Nirvita Shakya is a Visual artist based in Kathmandu. While she is widely known for Performance art and Fabric art, she is equally proficient in Oil painting, Mixed media painting, Ceramic art, Sculpting, Installation art.',5,'nirvitadp.jpg','2023-10-06 10:41:49','2023-10-06 10:50:01'),
(8,'Subash Poudel','subash-poudel','Musician','<h2>Subash Poudel is a dedicated musician and multi-instrumentalist who discovered his love for music during his school years.</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/subas1.jpg\" alt=\"Subash Poudel\" width=\"768\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Subash Poudel</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Subash Poudel is a dedicated musician and multi-instrumentalist who discovered his love for music during his school years. Beginning in 2008, he pursued his musical journey at Little Angels School, actively participating in various internal and inter-school musical events, including singing and music competitions, as well as performing in orchestral bands. Subash\'s musical journey continued as he joined Ace Higher Secondary School, where he co-founded the band Chakra Tandav, performing at underground events in Kathmandu\'s prominent venues like Gaa Hall and Bhrikutimandap.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>His passion and talent led him to become the bass guitarist of the progressive rock band White, which he joined alongside renowned guitarist Anil Dhital, Susant Bista and Sahil Risal. Subash spent four years with White, performing over 100 shows across the nation, including the prestigious Silence Festival where they shared the stage with international acts like Freak Kitchen and Mother Rockers Gang.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In 2013, Subash teamed up with his friend Susant to create the Wayam Duo Project, focusing on experimental Nepali folk indie progressive music. Their debut song, \"Aaye Baden Ma,\" featured collaborations with notable Nepali band Kutumba members, showcasing their unique fusion of styles. Subash\'s dedication to honing his skills led him to learn from Roshan Sharma, a respected guitarist and disciple of Grammy award winner Pandit Bishwa Mohan Bhatta.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Subsequently, Subash joined the band Urjaa with Roshan Sharma, releasing original songs and touring nationally and internationally, including India, Pakistan, and Dubai. In 2022, Subash and Susant\'s Wayam Duo Project released their debut album \"Sunne Lai Sun ko Mala,\" receiving enthusiastic responses from their fan base. Their single \"Udai Lanchu\" was a hit, both musically and visually, featuring a collaboration with Fuzz Factory Production for its video.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Beyond his musical endeavors, Subash also contributed to the field of music education, teaching at various international schools in Nepal. Taking a break from teaching, he joined Jazz Production in 2021, where he worked as a music composer, Foley artist, sound designer, and ADR for commercials of prominent national and multinational brands. Subash even played a role of sound recordist in the Nepali feature film \"Aina Jhyal Ko Putali,\" which received an official selection for the Oscar Awards.<br>Following two years at Jazz Production, Subash founded his production company, Mind Tunes Production, embarking on numerous projects, including background music for feature films. His journey is a testament to his unwavering dedication and passion for music and the arts.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/bc654880580642549b848d37ddf69c8c.jpg\" alt=\"Album lunch wayam udai lanchu\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Album lunch</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">wayam udai lanchu</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/8b2ed764e8bd4b0780376cbdc391ac54.jpg\" alt=\"Album lunch sunne lai sunko maala\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Album lunch<br>sunne lai sunko maala</span></p>','Subash Poudel is a dedicated musician and multi-instrumentalist who discovered his love for music during his school years. His passion and talent led him to become the bass guitarist of the progressive rock band White, which he joined alongside renowned guitarist Anil Dhital, Susant Bista and Sahil Risal.',6,'subas1.jpg','2023-10-06 10:51:18','2023-10-06 10:56:28'),
(9,'Bibek Lama (Blone)','bibek-lama-blone','Musician','<h2>In 2020 during lockdown, he got selected in the second edition of Confluence. There, he got an opportunity to work with Rochak Dahal and Subash Poudel and was introduced to many other versatile artists such as Suman Gautam, Aadesh Poudel and Darshika Regmi.</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/bibek3.jpg\" alt=\"Bibek Lama\" width=\"768px\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Bibek Lama</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Bibek Lama Blone is a Tungna player based in Kathmandu with a running Masters degree in Rural Development. He has been playing Tungna (Traditional Nepali lute) for half a decade. Besides this, he owns his youtube channel for more than 5 years where he frequently posts his covers and Tungna related videos. Bibek has been diving into Nepali folk music and has an aim on preserving and taking our age old music towards a new audience. Throughout his college years he worked as a volunteer in Shiksha Nepal with an aim to distribute Story books to children of remote areas of Nepal. Bibek believes these years as his shaping years where he got to meet an abundant number of young people and know about their thoughts. Which shifted his perception of life, society and culture.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>He first performed at Jamarko Jatra 2019 at Patan from Project Tungna which helped him to experience the joy of folk music. After that he Performed as background musician at Appearance of light 2019 with Sundar Lama, Sagun Tamang which led him into the world of performance art which he was unknown at that time. This led him to the profound impact of other mediums of art.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>He recalls this artform( performance art) changed his view towards art. After that, he performed at Utapala cafe for Muddy hands 2019 which led him to meet up with members of \"baaja\" musical group which further helped him to get into music. In 2020 during lockdown, he got selected in the second edition of Confluence. There, he got an opportunity to work with Rochak Dahal and Subash Poudel and was introduced to many other versatile artists such as Suman Gautam, Aadesh Poudel and Darshika Regmi. This co- learning and exchanging helped him to accept all genres of music and which supported him to develop incorporative habit of comradice. In 2022, he collaborated with Fret (a trio folk musical group from Bhaktapur) to perform his original \" Bhumari\" at Filhaal seto naadh organised by Project Naadhe. His song Bhumari illustrates his experience of gravitating compulsive cycle or patterns in life of which he doesn\'t seem happy. Deeply invoked with dark melody and hymns.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Similarly, he worked as a background musician for Sundar Lama\'s performance art \"Dancing grief\". Besides this, Bibek has been active as a session musician and has worked with various musicians including Darwin Lungeli, Rohit Shakya and many more. Bibek wishes to revoke the love of folk music and instruments in youths and also plans on releasing his music soon in the near future.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/2285521fc32c41869d75ed2373a42506.jpg\" alt=\"Project Sarangi\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Project Sarangi</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/56db427e18b04cd29d0645f2f58eae16.jpg\" alt=\"Performance art Appearance of light 2019\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Performance art Appearance of light 2019</span></p>','Bibek Lama Blone is a Tungna player based in Kathmandu with a running Masters degree in Rural Development. He has been playing Tungna (Traditional Nepali lute) for half a decade. Besides this, he owns his youtube channel for more than 5 years where he frequently posts his covers and Tungna related videos.',7,'bibek3.jpg','2023-10-06 10:58:25','2023-10-06 11:06:10'),
(10,'Sara Koinch','sara-koinch','Artist','<h2>From Childhhood memory, I was active in extra curriculum and try to do something different in life which has been meaningful entire life. My art journey began when I was at college and doing the job as a traditional thangka Artist for 3 years.</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"img-fluid\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../../uploads/sara.JPG\" alt=\"Sara Koinch\" width=\"512px\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Sara Koinch</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sara Tunich Koinch (Durga Sunuwar ) I am an art learner, art lover, and freelance artist. I was born in Shindhuli, 1991 December 2 then our family migrate from Shindhuli to Dhanusha. I completed slc from Shree Sarbjananik Higher Secondary School and studied +2 in management with a major in computer science at Mahendra Boudha Higher Secondary School. My Mother is a local market shopkeeper and my Father is a carpenter. I couldn\'t come with from a family an art background but art was always around me.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>From Childhood memory, I was active in extra curriculum and try to do something different in life which has been meaningful entire life. My art journey began when I was at college and doing the job as a traditional thangka Artist for 3 years . While I was in the traditional art field I was really curious about art and trying to know the pose of gods and goddesses and the meaning of color and theory and history. After the complete secondary level of education, I knew it was a fine art campus and decide to join.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In 2014 I joined the Lalit Kala Campus and completed my Bachelor\'s degree in painting as a major subject and done art volunteered in different art projects like Kathmandu Triennale and trans studio project 4.4 by Bikalpa art center. Started participating in Different art projects and workshops. I love all the forms of art on canvas I love to explore mural art in Different places. I had done different workshops like botanical illustrations 2014, save the Elephant, save the Earth which is Organized by apple international education 2016, The Object Artist and the Project vs subject creativity by(Theory and Praxis with nexus culture)2017, wall painting and Doodle workshops by Satya media group, Printmaking Etching Workshop by Nepal Printmaking Academy 2018, sculpture/wood Printmaking workshops by NAFA,2018, Art workshops and performance art by Karnali art center2018,7days wood sculpture workshops.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Pencil, Paper, canvas, color, and other mediums are major assests to explore my thinking and experience. Nowadays I Want to explore the other medium for my concept and subject that I choose. I have always been inclined Toward humans, society, and culture as the subject of my art. These days I am researching and doing my own culture because I want to know my own roots and my identity. So, art is a way to explore, create, invent, live, and express our feeling about us about society . For me art is free to anyone, and art is engaged anywhere any time day to day in our daily life. I am always inspired by different artists and the person, nowadays My inspirations are contemporary artists and art. In my Art journey, I Participated several National Art exhibitions like Alfresco Art Exhibition 2017/18 by Alfresco Magazine, National Art 2017-18-19, Season, women group exhibition 2019, and Commemorative Painting Workshop and Residency by bikalpa art cafe 2019, Virtual Nude Art Exhibition2020, ART AND MUSIC MELA 2021 and Karnali Ka Rangaharu2021, Virtual Exhibition Pray for myanmar2021 Indonesia, Young Artist show2021, poems from home2022, women Creative Energy 2022, Venue Team Coordinator/Exhibition Tour Guide in Kathmandu Triennale 2077, recently participated in group exhibitions women in action 2023 and windows to the sky by Takpa Art Gallery.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/c1500ffc40cb4f0ba376304221ccc705.JPG\" alt=\"Prominent Pattern\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Titile:Prominent Pattern</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Medium:Acrylic on Recharge card</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/85125b3b325f475bb5256704466cab9a.JPG\" alt=\"Prominent Pattern\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Titile:Prominent Pattern<br>Medium:Acrylic on Recharge card</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/36b8bead427640d0b011d5266d7fd1bc.JPG\" alt=\"Title: Parallel Journey Medium: Acrylic on Canvas Size : 3ft x 4ft\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Title: Parallel Journey<br>Medium: Acrylic on Canvas<br>Size : 3ft x 4ft</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/295803b5323544eea3ea0ebaf24c8235.JPG\" alt=\"Title: Parallel Journey Medium: Acrylic on Canvas Size : 3ft x 4ft\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Title: Parallel Journey<br>Medium: Acrylic on Canvas<br>Size : 3ft x 4ft</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/bcf58a6477ee4c7cbff1400c3e7767cb.JPG\" alt=\"Title:urbanizing cultural values Medium:Acrylic on canvas Size:4ftx4ft\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Title:urbanizing cultural values<br>Medium:Acrylic on canvas<br>Size:4ftx4ft</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/cee61bf663574aaa845d2bed75736c75.jpg\" alt=\"Title:urbanizing cultural values Medium:Acrylic on canvas Size:3ftx4ft\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Title:urbanizing cultural values<br>Medium:Acrylic on canvas<br>Size:3ftx4ft</span></p>','Sara Tunich Koinch (Durga Sunuwar) is a versatile artist known for her fervent exploration of diverse mediums, capturing the essence of human experience and culture. From traditional thangka art to contemporary masterpieces, her journey began during her college life.',8,'sara.JPG','2023-10-06 11:07:47','2023-10-06 11:17:00'),
(12,'Poojan Gyawali','poojan-gyawali','Poet','<h2>What I\'ve created till now are all epitome of reality I\'ve lived. These are all the reflections. I don\'t understand sometimes these concepts are very abstract and complex yet - they arrived because they were real at some point.</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/pg1.jpg\" alt=\"Poojan Gyawali\" width=\"512px\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Poojan Gyawali</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Poojan Gyawali is a visionary poet who crafts verses that defy conventional understanding , inviting us into a realm of thoughts where boundaries dissolve. His poems are abstract and he believes an artist roots are the most powerful element of their creation. \"Kagajkodunga\", \"The Last Dream\", \" ghau \" are poozan\'s major work in poetry which are reflection of his artistic .</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Poojan have worked with various artist. He was also a part of Project Naadhe. He collaborated with poet \"sabinbataule\" in Project Naadhe. Together, they meld perspectives and ideas, illuminating the profound interplay between internal and external state of poets. Through this synergy, Poozan and Bataule performed a mural of emotions that invited introspection and provoked contemplation.They performed a poetry \"Kagaz ra kabita\" together. Poojan also have contributed to RPPS\'s \"Ritu Utsab\" event, where he recited \"Kagajkodunga.\"</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Poojan says - Art has never been two plus two equalsto five for me. It\'s always four. What I\'ve created till now are all epitome of reality I\'ve lived. These are all the reflections. I don\'t understand sometimes these concepts are very abstract and complex yet - they arrived because they were real at some point.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/27e666eaae134a9db637d23b6f9a7b31.jpg\" alt=\"From &quot; Kagaj ra Kabita &quot; Purano Ghar Theater\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">From \" Kagaj ra Kabita \"</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Purano Ghar Theater</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../../uploads/a3f0d0f4cce9430b8b1ba0900d8dfedd.jpeg\" alt=\"From Kagajkodunga\" width=\"1024px\" height=\"auto\"></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">From Kagajkodunga</span></p>','Poojan Gyawali is a visionary poet who crafts verses that defy conventional understanding , inviting us into a realm of thoughts where boundaries dissolve.',9,'pg1.jpg','2023-10-06 11:19:29','2023-10-06 11:23:47');

